  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 546 mg
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Slice the @demi-baguette{1} into ¾-inch cubes. Toss the bread cubes on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{½%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place baking sheet in the oven to toast for ~{5-7%minutes}, until golden brown but still soft in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve, pit, and thinly slice the @nectarine{1}. Thinly slice the @shallot{1}. Using a #vegetable peeler{}, shave the @zucchini{1} into ribbons lengthwise, rotating as necessary. Toss the zucchini ribbons in a #large bowl{} with @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove the bread cubes from the oven to cool. Slice half the @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into ½-inch cubes. Chop the @mint{¼%oz} leaves. TIP: Save the remaining mozzarella for the next time you make this recipe, or any other recipe that calls for it.

Make the vinaigrette: in a #small bowl{}, combine the shallot, remaining @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, and @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the mozzarella, bread cubes, mint, @arugula{2%oz}, nectarine, and vinaigrette to the bowl with the zucchini. Toss to combine, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and enjoy!

> Just toss the arugula and mint in right before serving! This panzanella is even better if made a few hours in advance.